      <section id="details">
        <h2 class="gem-c-heading gem-c-heading--font-size-27 gem-c-heading--mobile-top-margin  ">Details</h2>


        
<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak direction-ltr" data-module="govspeak">
      <div class="govspeak">
<p>Different employment conditions affect you employeeâ€™s eligibility for the Job Support Scheme.</p>

<p>Find out if you can claim, if your employee:</p>

<ul>
  <li>has more than one job</li>
  <li>is on or has just returned from statutory parental leave</li>
  <li>gets Maternity Allowance</li>
  <li>is ending maternity leave early to claim through the Job Support Scheme</li>
  <li>goes on sick leave while on the Job Support Scheme</li>
  <li>is on a fixed term contract</li>
  <li>is an apprentice</li>
  <li>does volunteer work</li>
  <li>does training</li>
  <li>stopped working for you after 23 September 2020 and you then rehire them</li>
  <li>has been transferred under TUPE and or a change in ownership</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

      </section>
